<overview>
Sapper is an old term for combat engineers, especially those involved with explosives, demolitions, and mines.  These activities are conducted in peacetime, such as EOD (explosive ordnance disposal) and clearing leftover minefields, as well as breaching minefields and destroying critical bunkers and bridges while under active fire.
</overview>

